+# Step-012 Scope Lock Remains Menu Level Without One Theorem Facing Observable And Leverage Claim
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` Step-012 verdict with `INFERRED` missing-piece diagnosis
+
+The Step-012 record narrows honestly to one provisional triple:
+`local concentration of active scales`
++ `backward stochastic flow / back-to-label transport`
++ `stochastic back-to-label observable`.
+
+That is still not a real mechanism-family-observable lock.
+
+The remaining obstruction is specific:
+
+- the branch has not frozen one theorem-facing observable packet;
+- it has not frozen one sentence explaining how that observable acts on the
+  chosen burden beyond expectation-only rewriting;
+- and the archive still allows the decisive leverage question to stay at
+  representation level instead of estimate level.
+
+So the correct filing is `menu-level setup obstruction`, not a passed Step-1
+entry into exact-identity expansion.
+
+Filed from:
