+# Stochastic Back To Label Observable Is The Most Concrete Name On Disk But Still Not A Frozen Packet
+
+Status: `INFERRED` most concrete observable label with `VERIFIED` incompleteness
+
+The most concrete candidate observable name on the Step-012 local record is the
+named `stochastic back-to-label observable`.
+
+But the record still stops short of a usable observable packet:
+
+- no exact formula is frozen on disk;
+- no localization or stopping protocol is frozen with it;
+- no theorem-facing insertion point is fixed;
+- and no explicit gain sentence says why this observable should constrain the
+  chosen burden beyond expectation-level rewriting.
+
+So the repository has a serious observable name, but not yet one concrete
+observable packet that could clear the Step-1 admissibility bar.
+
+Filed from:
